    150          
    151          // Inter-PAN messages are a security risk because they are typically not
    152          // encrypted and yet we must accept them.  Therefore, we are very strict about
    153          // what we allow.  Listed below are ZCL messages that are allowed, including
    154          // the profile, cluster, direction, and command id.  Any inter-PAN messages not
    155          // matching one of these are dropped.
    156          // If inter-PAN fragments (IPMF) are received, a different set of checks is
    157          // performed.

   \                                 In section .rodata, align 4
